Follow all these rules, and you'll wind up with reasonably efficient production. Note that they ALL need to be followed.

== Transport ==

Once collected, natural resources (wood, stone, iron, and food) may be transported around your empire through the use of carts (managed by the Marketplace) or trading ships (managed by the Harbor). Gold, however, is considered an empire-wide resource, and therefore does not need to be moved between cities. Also, warehouses do not benefit the extra storage for gold, thus gold has no maximum amount. You can accumulate Gold forever and beyond.
